    "original_title": "Manhattan: Cabrini Boulevard - 181st Street (West)",
    "text": "Cabrini Blvd., west side, north of W 181st Street, showing the estate of Dr. Chas V. Paterno being cleared, preparatory to the construction of a 12 story detached apartment structure which will cost $6,000,000; Geo. Fred Pelham Jr. being the architect. The castle-like home of this real-estate dealer was\nbuilt of white marble in 1908 in a combined form of Roman and English architecture and is stated to have cost $500,00.\nNote the George Washington Bridge and the Jersey highlands in the background.\nAugust 23, 1938.\nViews 1, 2 and 3\nP.L. Sperr\n",
